        "timestamp": "2017-09-15 13:56:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThe problem with this is that if sdnc/core (which builds the sli) is a newer version than sdnc/northbound, you'll end up looking for an older version of the sli.\n\nWhat we might want to do instead is just remove the version entirely from that <feature> tag.  I don't recall why we added that there, but removing it might be a better change",
